    'farmersmarket:301755',
    'Brookside Farmers Market - Summer',
    'Brookside Farmers’ Market is an sustainable, regenerative, pesticide-free local, producer-only market. Producers use organic, sustainable and cruelty-free practices, travel less than 125 miles to market, and those who grow, raise or make every product are the ones who sell it to you directly. Each Saturday you will find just-picked, farm-fresh vegetables and herbs, bright flowers, delicious meats, eggs from free-range chickens, freshly prepared breads and baked goods including many vegan and gluten-free items, fresh juices, and a place to sit and take in the scene. The market has brought farm fresh produce to the Brookside neighborhood and beyond since 2003. The market is located at HJ''s Community Center and is open Saturdays 8 a.m. to 1 p.m. through October 31. Check website for WINTER MARKET dates, hours, and location.',
