    (
    'farmersmarket:301497',
    'Pleasantville Farmers Market - Outdoor',
    'The largest weekly, year-round farmers market in the county, voted "Best of Westchester" in 2014 - 2025, twelve years in a row! With over 60 vendors, 9 nearby parking lots, live music, culinary demos, kids events, and nutritional talks, the Market is located in Memorial Plaza, in the heart of the historic Village of Pleasantville. Please note the Market is a dog-free environment. SNAP benefits are doubled (up to $40) at Pleasantville Farmers Market. Redeem $40 in benefits, get $80 to spend, thanks to a generous grant from our local hospitals, Phelps Hospital and Northern Westchester Hospital, both part of the Market''s Lead Sponsor Northwell Health. WIC & Seniors Farmers Market Nutrition Program checks can also be used to purchase fruit and vegetables at the Market. Stop by the Managers Tent for assistance.',
